[h1]The background-attachment Property[/h1]

The background-attachment property sets whether a background image is fixed or scrolls with the rest of the page.
Even if an element has a scrolling mechanism, a "fixed" background doesn't move with the element.

[b]The CSS:[/b][code format="css" codeId="551"]body {
   background-image: url("css_logo.png");
   background-repeat: no-repeat;
   [b]background-attachment: fixed[/b];
}[/code]
[b]Result: [/b][img id="2632" width="100%"]

[h1]The background-attachment Values[/h1]

You can also set the background-attachment to [b]inherit[/b] or [b]scroll[/b].
When you set the background-attachment to [b]inherit[/b], it will inherit the value from its parent element. 

When you set the background-attachment to [b]scroll[/b], the background image will scroll with the rest of the content.

[b]The CSS:[/b][code format="css" codeId="552"]body {
   background-image: url("css_logo.png");
   background-repeat: no-repeat;
  [b] background-attachment: scroll;[/b]
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2633" width="100%"]
